						<summary>

						<p>Fragments of a stone lying in the temple of Mādhavasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 16th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It mentions Vīrapratāpa • • • varāya Mahārāya and refers to the 24 families <hi rend="italic">(kulas)</hi> of the bōyas.</p>						

